
Overview of noun decision

The noun decision has 5 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (25) decision, determination, conclusion -- (the act of making up your mind about something; "the burden of decision was his"; "he drew his conclusions quickly")
2. (10) decision, determination, conclusion -- (a position or opinion or judgment reached after consideration; "a decision unfavorable to the opposition"; "his conclusion took the evidence into account"; "satisfied with the panel's determination")
3. (2) decision -- ((boxing) a victory won on points when no knockout has occurred; "had little trouble in taking a unanimous decision over his opponent")
4. (1) decision -- (the outcome of a game or contest; "the team dropped three decisions in a row")
5. decisiveness, decision -- (the trait of resoluteness as evidenced by firmness of character or purpose; "a man of unusual decisiveness")
